Load the Database¶

what we're trying to do is

  • Access Data via API
  • Convert Data to JSON
  • Normalize Data
In [32]:
#Access Data via API
conn = http.client.HTTPSConnection("api.covid19api.com") #COVID 19 API
payload = ''
headers = {}
conn.request("GET", "/summary", payload, headers)
res = conn.getresponse()
data = res.read().decode('UTF-8')
In [33]:
covid1=json.loads(data) #loads the Data
In [35]:
df= pd.DataFrame(covid1['Countries']) #normalize the data
df;
In [36]:
covid2 = df.drop(columns =['CountryCode','Slug','Date','Premium'],axis=1) 
#to drop unnecessary columns

Generate Base Map¶

In [37]:
m = folium.Map(tiles="Stamen Terrain", min_zoom=1.5);
In [38]:
#obtaining Geodata
url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/python-visualization/folium/master/examples/data'
country_shapes = f'{url}/world-countries.json'

Generating Choropleth Map Layer¶

In [40]:
folium.Choropleth(
    geo_data=country_shapes,
    min_zoom=2,
    name='COVID-19',
    data=covid2,
    columns=['Country', 'TotalConfirmed'],
    key_on='feature.properties.name',
    fill_color='OrRd',
    nan_fill_color='black',
    legend_name='Total Confirmed Covid Cases',
).add_to(m);
m;

In [41]:
covid2.update(covid2['TotalConfirmed'].map('Total Confirmed:{}'.format))
covid2.update(covid2['TotalRecovered'].map('Total Recovered:{}'.format))
In [22]:

coordinates;
In [21]:
covid_final= pd.merge(covid2,coordinates,on='Country')
In [19]:
def plotDot(point):
    folium.CircleMarker(location=[point.latitude, point.longitude],
                        radius=5,
                        weight=2,
                        popup = [point.Country,point.TotalConfirmed,point.TotalRecovered],
                        fill_color='#000000').add_to(m);

Total Confirmed Case & Total Recovered with Circle Marks¶

In [42]:
covid_final.apply(plotDot, axis = 1)

m.fit_bounds(m.get_bounds())

m

Adding Circular Marker into a Heat Map¶

In [51]:
def plotDot(point):
    folium.CircleMarker(location=[point.latitude, point.longitude],
                        radius=5,
                        weight=2,
                        popup = [point.Country,point.TotalDeaths],
                        fill_color='#000000').add_to(m1)

covid_final.apply(plotDot, axis = 1)

m1.fit_bounds(m1.get_bounds())

m1
